  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Site Manager</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Visit www.ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor project progress and address any delays proactively.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with the Project Manager to align with project goals.</li>\n  <li>Oversee all on-site construction activities including material procurement, subcontractor management, and workforce allocation.</li>\n  <li>Ensure availability of materials, equipment, and manpower for smooth progress.</li>\n  <li>Manage site costs, track expenses, and optimise resource use to stay within budget.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site visits to assess progress, quality, and compliance with specifications.</li>\n  <li>Plan and manage site facilities like access and storage areas.</li>\n  <li>Ensure construction complies with design specs, contracts, building codes, and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Conduct safety audits, risk assessments, and enforce safety protocols to prevent accidents.</li>\n  <li>Maintain compliance with health, safety, welfare, and environmental laws.</li>\n  <li>Lead, supervise, and motivate the site team and subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Plan ahead to solve problems and resolve conflicts on site.</li>\n  <li>Analyse and manage project risks.</li>\n  <li>Implement process improvements when necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, Building Science, or related field (Bachelor’s preferred for senior roles).</li>\n  <li>5 to 10 years’ experience in construction site management or similar role.</li>\n  <li>Experience managing various construction projects (residential, commercial, infrastructure, HDB, LTA, DSTA) preferred depending on company focus.</li>\n  <li>Strong leadership skills to manage and motivate diverse teams and subcontractors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Take charge of construction projects—apply today!</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Visit www.ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>",
